summary: Black people’s mental health is always mocked, ignored, and even posed as a threat both in and out of our community. These...
body:
Black people’s mental health is always mocked, ignored, and even posed as a threat both in and out of our community. These things need to be taken seriously, and not every time we loose them once the battle is lost.

Dunno how many of you’ve heard about it, but a YouTuber/Twitch streamer Etika was officially found dead recently. He was missing since Wednesday and reports said they found his body after he took his own life by drowning. I’m bringing this up because I want to highlight some of his words in a video he made:

How he expressed he pushed everyone away

How he felt no one would miss him

How he said he took “being edgy” too far & it ruined his life

And how he felt the walls were closing in on him before his left.

He even said that he didn’t always have depression. Or at least he didn’t know it. And that right there lies the problem. We go about our lives believing our suffering is just apart of life, that it’s apart of “the struggle”. It’s one thing to go through hardships, but suffering in silence without help is our biggest downfall and a poison even to the healthiest person.

I know there’s a lot of us out there who probably don’t care nor know about Etika or his content, but if anything that you can take out of this, please please take care of yourself and the people around you. Reach out to the people that shares your common interests. Take your meds, keep note about your behavior and be kind and patient with yourself when it comes to developing your recovery process.

My heart goes out to him and his family. Depression and mental illnesses need to be taken seriously within the community without violence or aggression. Don’t put that shit off just because you don’t wanna deal with it or don’t want to believe it’s happening to you. Acknowledging there’s a problem is the first step to recovery and the path to seek help.

Spread love and support while everyone is here instead of after they’re gone.

summary: Mental Health is NOT a game
title: Mental Health is NOT a game
body:
Yesterday, the New York Police labelled Desmond Amofah, better known as Etika on Youtube missing.

Today a few minutes ago, NYPD confirmed Desmond as dead.

He’s had a past with mental health issues consisting of mental breakdowns, suicide threats which lead to NYPD having to shutdown parts of Manhattan.

I may not be the best person to talk about this but if you or anyone you know is having mental health issues or seems suicidal you and they are not alone, and you deserve a second chance.

Hotlines, by country

America- 1-800-273-8255 

Spain- 717 003 717 

UK- 0808 802 58 58

Portugal- 225 50 60 70 

Italy- 800 86 00 22 or 06 77208977 

Russia- 007 (8202) 577-577

summary:
Varios modelos de Smartphones se quedaran sin WhatsApp dentro de este año.

La razón es sencilla: dichas actualizaciones...
caption:
Varios modelos de Smartphones se quedaran sin WhatsApp dentro de este año.

La razón es sencilla: dichas actualizaciones necesitan más recursos de los que estos celulares pueden ofrecer. Así queda la lista:

Android: los celulares con OS 2.3.3 o anterior ya no podrán usar la app.

iPhone: Quedarán obsoletos en cuanto a WhatsApp se refiere los celulares con iOS 8 o anteriores.

Windows Phone: Para que la app siga funcionando, el celular deberá tener mínimo WP 8.1.

Nokia: Por su parte, los equipos Nokia S40 ya no podrán usar la app a partir del 31 d diciembre del 2019; aunque para esto aún falta más tiempo.

Esto fue confirmado por la aplicación en su página de preguntas y respuestas; por lo que hablamos de información oficial, aunque aún no hay una fecha exacta. 

Si tienes alguno equipo con estas características; quizá sea hora de ir pensando en actualizarte.
